          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Many of ICA Miami=
=E2=80=99s exhibitions came about because the museum acquired work by these=
 artists very early. =E2=80=9CWe have been, in many cases, unafraid,=E2=80=
=9D Gartenfeld said, =E2=80=9Cto be the first institution to collect, which=
 has been, I=E2=80=99d say, advantageous for a museum that doesn=E2=80=99t =
have unlimited resources.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>The ability of a decade-old mu=
seum to acquire work at all, let alone before other institutions and collec=
tors, requires a large and engaged board. And, indeed, Gartenfeld=E2=80=99s=
 true masterstroke was an ability to position ICA Miami at the center of th=
e city=E2=80=99s collecting community, acting as both a common context and =
a coordinating council among its affluent collectors. =E2=80=9CI guess it i=
s all about community building,=E2=80=9D Gartenfeld said. =E2=80=9CIn the l=
ast decade, there=E2=80=99s been a major perceptual flip on Miami as a seri=
ous cultural anchor.
And that wasn=E2=80=99t incidental.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Put simply, the grow=
th in the city=E2=80=99s cultural infrastructure came about because Miami d=
ecided to take itself more seriously. But Gartenfeld believes that the foun=
dation was laid long before that via Miami=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cdeep bench=E2=
=80=9D of collectors dating back to the <b>Cisneros</b>, <b>Rubell</b>, <b>=
Margulies</b>, <b>de la Cruz</b>, and <b>Braman </b>families=E2=80=94the ve=
ry locus of activity that brought Art Basel to Miami Beach two decades ago.=
<br/><br/>Gartenfeld has spent the last 11 years working closely with local=
 collectors through the city and the art scene=E2=80=99s evolution. =E2=80=
=9CThe collections that they=E2=80=99ve built are truly accomplished and ex=
traordinary,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CThey just happen to be in private p=
laces. And we=E2=80=99ve tried to demonstrate how those great collections c=
an effectively collaborate with the institutions. I think that=E2=80=99s a =
key stage of growth in the city. I do think that we=E2=80=99ve been exempla=
ry at doing that and
presenting that collaboration.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
